[[!meta title="Installing additional fonts"]]

You can install additional fonts in Tails to use in *LibreOffice*, *Inkscape*, or *GIMP*.

To do so:

1. Turn on the [[Dotfiles|persistent_storage/configure#dotfiles]] feature of
   the Persistent Storage.

1. Choose **Places&nbsp;▸ Dotfiles** from the top navigation bar to open the
   *Dotfiles* folder in the *Files* browser.

1. Choose **[[!img lib/open-menu.png alt="Menu" class="symbolic"
   link="no"]]&nbsp;▸ Show Hidden Files** in the *Files* browser to display
   hidden files and folders.

1. Create a new folder named *.fonts* (notice the `.`) in this *Dotfiles* folder.

1. Store the fonts that you want to persist in this *.fonts* folder.

   You can store TTF and ODT fonts.

1. Restart Tails.
